description:
&lt;p&gt;We have a post for an experienced Clinical/Counselling Psychologist to join the Adult Psychology Service (APS) working closely with MDT on providing assessment, consultation, supervision and psychological interventions to our Community Mental Health Team based in Southbourne and Christchurch. The Adult Psychology Service (APS) is an innovative department providing psychological service to the CMHTs. We offer a psychological programme aligned with a disorder specific pathway.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post-holder will have the responsibility to provide psychological assessment, treatments and support the MDT with consultation, case formulation, reflective practice and supervision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would welcome applications from both newly qualified psychologists and those that are already currently working in a Band 7 position. With this role, we provide a very comprehensive and fully supported Preceptorship Programme that will allow the candidate to progress to a Band 8a over a set period of time depending on previous experience and meeting certain set milestones/objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder must have a car that is suitable for business use.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in moving to Dorset we also offer a generous relocation package of up to £5,000. For further details on relocation expenses please email dhc.careers@nhs.net.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Employment in these posts require an Enhanced Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) check. The DBS levies a charge of £40 and the Trust will recover this cost in instalments from your first 3 salary payments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants who subscribe to the DBS update service and are able to present a valid DBS certificate will not incur a charge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact: Shelagh Webb, Bank Business Support Assistant - Adult Psychology Service at shelagh.webb1@nhs.net / 07884 116345.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal enquiries and visits are welcomed, please contact Dr Lilian Garcia-Roberts (Clinical Lead, Adult Psychology Service &amp; Inpatient) at lilian.garcia-roberts@nhs.net.&lt;/p&gt;
